About the Job
        
                Organization: Accenture Federal Services
Location: Annapolis Junction, MD
Accenture Federal Services, a wholly owned subsidiary of Accenture LLP, is a U.S. company that helps clients transform bold ideas into breakthrough outcomes. We serve every cabinet-level department and 30 of the largest federal organizations. Our 9,000 dedicated colleagues and change makers work with clients at the heart of the nation's priorities in defense, intelligence, public safety, civilian and health to make a difference for the people they employ, serve, and protect.
The Data Scientist Manager will enjoy working in fast paced environment with large-scale mission critical data, latest machine learning technologies, and the ability to turn ideas into actionable products for homeland security. Individuals in this role are expected to be working directly with customers, have passion for solving complex problem sets, work independently and collaboratively with team members experienced with Agile methodology.
(i) Drive technical modeling, research and product development activities;
(ii) Identify opportunities for impact to shape project, technical and management consideration;
(iii) Develop advanced algorithms, search models and address challenges to establish large-scale information retrieval and recommender systems;
(iv) Provide expertise in quantitative analysis, data mining and statistical methods to build specialized models, services and tools using machine learning methods and distributed computing;
(v) Mine large amounts of data, develop information retrieval systems, search models and work products to solve problem sets involving entity resolution with messy data and sparse data sets;
